{
  "stem": "25639.10",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And one day, my mother wrote to me that as much as we would love to have you come home, we think that you will have a much better life in America.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "You see, because the Soviets occupied also my birthplace.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "What was Czechoslovakia became Hungary, and what was Hungary now became the Ukraine part of the Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And eventually the Soviet Union closed the borders.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And nobody could go in or out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And [SIGHS] so mother felt that I'd have a better life here than I would have in the Soviet Union, where there were many hardships to be endured yet, for those who survived.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And so I listened to my mother with pain in my heart, knowing that I would never see her again.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] But these words were spoken with great love, I know.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "[SOBBING] Because only a mother could advise her child under those circumstances not to come home and knowing that we may never see each other again.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my relatives, of course, immediately after learning that I was alive, applied for [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] eventually immigration for me.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And prior to that, before I knew about either my American relatives or my family's survival, I felt that if nobody is alive, should there be such an eventuality, I cannot stay in Sweden.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No matter how lovely people are, and how wonderful this country is, I felt that I have to be with my people, and that I want to help build a new land, where discrimination and hatred and prejudice against my people will never be the case.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so I've-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] my Zionist background has come-- has played a big role in that.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
